## Core Features (Detailed)

### 1. Account & Onboarding

| Feature | What it does |
|--------|----------------|
| Sign up | Create account with name, email, password |
| Log in | Email/password authentication |
| Forgot password | Reset password via email link |
| Welcome screen | First-time users see intro; returning users go to login |
| 3-step tutorial | Explains posting, sharing, and community support after signup |
| Stay logged in | App remembers login so users return faster |
| Log out | Sign out from profile |
| Delete account | Permanently remove account and associated data |

---

### 2. Home Feed (Main Story Stream)

The heart of Haven.

- Shows community stories, **newest first**
- Each card shows: title, author (or “Anonymous User”), optional location, text preview, and media
- **Sensitive stories** are blurred until the user taps to reveal
- **Scheduled stories** stay hidden until their publish time
- Empty state when no stories exist yet
- Header with **search** and **notifications** (with unread badge)
- Bottom navigation: **Home, New Post, Fun Activities, Profile**

---

### 3. Creating & Managing Stories

**Creating a post**
- Rich text editor (bold, formatting, paragraphs)
- Add **photos** or **videos** (uploaded to cloud storage)
- Optional **tags** in the UI (used for title hints; full tag persistence is limited)
- **Post anonymously** — shows as “Anonymous User” with a ghost avatar
- **Allow / disable comments** per story
- **Mark as sensitive** — blurred in feed until revealed
- **Schedule for later** — story publishes at a chosen date/time

**After publishing**
- Story appears in the feed (when not scheduled)
- Author gets an in-app “published” notification
- Others can like, comment, bookmark, and read it

**Managing own stories**
- View all stories on profile (last 2 shown + “See all” for full list)
- **Edit** title, text, privacy settings, schedule
- **Delete** with confirmation; related likes, comments, bookmarks, and reads are cleaned up
- **Reader count** — author sees how many unique people opened the story (author’s own views don’t count)

---

### 4. Reading & Engaging With Stories

**Story detail screen**
- Full story text (HTML rendered)
- Image carousel or video player with play/pause, mute, progress
- Like and bookmark
- Share via device share sheet
- Open comments
- Author-only: edit, delete, see reader count

**Comments**
- Bottom-sheet style comment panel
- Top-level comments and **replies** (threaded)
- Add text; image attachment UI exists (full cloud upload for comment images is not fully wired)
- Comment likes work in the UI but are **not saved to the database yet**
- If comments are disabled on a story, the comment UI respects that

**Likes & bookmarks**
- Optimistic updates (UI changes immediately)
- Author gets in-app notifications for likes and bookmarks (not for self-actions)

**Reader tracking**
- Opening a story records one read per user per story
- Author viewing their own story does **not** increase the count
- Re-opening the same story does **not** count again

---

### 5. Profile & Identity

- **Avatar** — pick from preset icons (cat, dog, bird, etc.), not required to use a real photo
- **Display name** and **bio**
- **Stats**: total stories, unique readers across stories, total likes received
- **My Stories** — recent 2 on profile; full list on separate screen
- **Saved stories** — bookmarked posts
- **Liked stories** — posts the user liked
- **Edit profile** — name, bio, avatar
- **Settings** — account, privacy, help, terms

---

### 6. Notifications

In-app notification center (no push notifications yet).

**Types**
- Someone liked your story
- Someone commented on your story
- Someone replied to your comment
- Someone saved your story
- Your story was published
- Your story was deleted

**Behavior**
- Grouped as “Today” and “Earlier”
- Unread count on the bell icon (shows “9+” when over 9)
- Opening notifications marks them as read
- Tapping can navigate to the related story

---

### 7. Search & Discovery

- Search by story title, author name, or story text
- Debounced search (waits briefly while typing)
- **Trending topics** — popular words from recent stories as tappable chips
- Tap a result to open the full story

---

### 8. Fun Activities

Separate section from the story feed.

- Curated list of educational games and learning sites
- Grouped into sections (e.g. Trending Today, Top games, Continue Playing)
- Each item: icon, title, short description, external link
- Opens in the device browser
- Pull to refresh; skeleton while loading

Examples of linked activities: math games, science exploration, storytelling tools, early learning platforms.

---

### 9. Settings, Privacy & Security

**Settings hub**
- Edit profile
- Privacy & security
- Help center
- Terms of service

**Privacy & security screen**
- Private account toggle (stored; **no follower system yet**, so not fully enforced)
- Activity status toggle (stored; not fully enforced in UI)
- Allow tagging toggle (tagging feature not built yet)
- Strict content filter toggle (stored; not applied to feed filtering yet)
- Change password (re-authenticate, then update)
- Download account data as JSON (via share sheet)
- Delete account

**Help & legal**
- Help center with FAQ-style layout (mostly static placeholders)
- Full terms of service (age 13+, community rules, etc.)

---

### 10. Media & Content Safety

- **Photos and videos** uploaded to cloud storage before publish
- **Sensitive content gate** — blur + tap to reveal in feed and detail
- **Anonymous mode** — hides real name and uses anonymous avatar
- **Comment control** — author can turn comments off per story
- **Scheduled publishing** — content goes live only at the chosen time

