## Data Model (Conceptual)

**Users & profiles**
- Each account has one profile: name, avatar choice, bio, optional location.

**Stories**
- Title, HTML body, optional media (JSON list of images/videos), anonymous flag, sensitive flag, comment allowance, optional schedule time, author link.

**Engagement**
- Story likes (one per user per story)
- Story bookmarks (saves)
- Story reads (unique viewers per story)
- Comments with optional parent for replies
- Comment likes (schema exists; app not fully using it)

**Notifications**
- Per-user inbox: type, message, related story/comment, read/unread, who triggered it.

**User settings**
- Privacy toggles stored per user.

**Fun activities**
- Standalone curated items: title, description, link, icon styling, section label.

**Storage**
- Post media in cloud storage; public URLs stored on stories.

**Security model**
- Stories and profiles are publicly readable.
- Only the author can edit or delete their stories.
- Likes, bookmarks, reads, and notifications are scoped to the right user.
- Account deletion removes profile data and cascades to related content.

